attributes.description: This dashboard displays detailed information about three different types of stop errors: blue screen of death, hard power off and random restart. A blue screen is displayed when the system detects it cannot continue due to an error condition and stops after collecting rudimentary information. A hard power off happens when the user presses and holds the power button for at least 4 seconds. A random restart may be due to power loss or a hard hang; in either case the system cannot generate a blue screen any more.
